author: Inside Edition
description: The man suspected of carrying out the Brown University shooting and the murder of an MIT professor, 48-year-old Claudio Neves Valente, shot himself in the head at police closed in. Syracuse University professor Scott Watson gave insight into the shooter's personality. Watson was Valente's best friend. They were graduate students together at Brown in 2000. Valente studied nuclear physics in Lisbon in the same class as MIT professor, Nuno Loureiro, who he later murdered.
title: What Was The Brown University, MIT Professor Shooter's Motive?

author: Inside Edition
description: The bear who moved into the crawlspace under a house seems to have found his forever home. It has been 32 days since the giant bear barricaded himself at a home in Altadena, California. Homeowner Ken Johnson tells Inside Edition he is at his wit's end. A bear trap has been positioned by Fish and Game in the driveway, but the bear has not taken the bait. In an Inside Edition "oops" moment, the crew may have accidentally triggered the trap by getting too close.
title: Bear Still Living Under California Home 32 Days Later

author: Inside Edition
description: An elementary school teacher kept crying while learning her fate for her obsessive relationship with an 11-year-old student. The judge in Wisconsin asked her to compose herself. Madison Bergmann, 26, was accused of texting the student 35,000 times. To the victim, Bergmann said she takes "full responsibility for every boundary that was crossed." The boy did not appear in court but his father did. Bergmann was sentenced to six years in prison.
title: Teacher Who Texted 11-Year-Old 35,000 Times Gets 6 Years In Prison

author: Inside Edition
description: Alina Silver auditioned to be a Radio City Rockette while she was seven-and-a-half months pregnant. She got a round of applause as she showed off her baby bump. Silver got the job. She had a baby named Amanda and got right in the famous kick line with her fellow Rockettes at the Macy's Thanksgiving Day Parade. The audition was in 2016, but Silver posted about it Tuesday, and it went viral. Amanda is now 9 years old.
title: Woman Auditioned For Radio City Rockettes While 7 Months Pregnant

author: Inside Edition
description: Video captures a man leaping into water after a plane crashed killing at least five people. His name is Sky Decker and his 11-year-old son Sky Jr, shot the video. The plane was en route to Galveston, Texas. The passengers included a 2-year-old who was flying to the US for treatment for burns. Many Americans are traveling by road for the holiday. AAA says a record 110 million vehicles are expected to hit the road over Christmas and New Year. Inside Edition spoke to AAA's Robert Sinclair.
title: Video Captures Man Jumping Into Action After Plane Crash

author: Inside Edition
description: These alleged thieves may have bit off more than they could chew. This video was released by cops in the Town of Greece, New York. They say it shows a pickup truck pull over and two men get out. They then proceed to load snow blowers into the bed of the truck. This plan may have sounded easier than it was. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Alleged Thieves Tie Snowblowers To Pickup Truck And Drive Away

author: Inside Edition
description: The creator of some of the world's most popular video games has died. Electronic Arts announced that Vince Zampella, who was behind such titles as Call of Duty, passed away on Sunday. CBS News reports that Zampella died when his Ferrari crashed on the Angeles Crest Highway, in Los Angeles. A passenger in the car also died in the incident. Zampella was the former CEO of Infinity Ward, the gaming studio behind the "Call of Duty" franchise.
title: 'Call Of Duty' Creator Dies In Ferrari Crash

author: Inside Edition
description: Newly released video shows Anna Kepner and other cruise passengers doing the 'Cupid Shuffle' during the Sail Away Party, a gathering as the ship leaves port.
title: Cruise Ship Video Shows Anna Kepner Days Before Her Death #shorts
